12/12/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- The NATO foreign ministers issued a statement Saturday (11 December) urging Albania, Croatia and Macedonia to continue implementing integration reforms. 
The ministers, who met on Wednesday and Thursday, praised the progress made by the three countries so far, but noted much remains to be done.
In other news, Albania invited outgoing US Secretary of State Colin Powell to the May meeting of Albania, Croatia and Macedonia on NATO integration. 
(ATA - 11/12/04; ATA - 10/12/04)
